  "description": [
    "Doctors Plan Big New Clinic As Example of Group Practice By John McKelway A group of Washington doc tors are pooling their talents plan by the fall of 1954 to give this city another example of a new trend in medicine group practice The doctors both specialists and general practitioners feel the public is demanding this type of medicine Ten doctors will occupy what is to be known as The Wash ington Clinic Six other doctors will make up the consulting group They hope to be open for business by September or October 1954 The clinic a threestory build ing is to be located on a trian gular tract of land formed by the intersection of Military road and Western avenue NWjust east of Wisconsin avenue Cost of the building has been esti mated at 400000 and construc tion is expected to begin in October or November It has been roughly six years in the making Similar to Mayo Clinie The operational plan of the clinic follows the same lines of the famous Mayo Clinic in Rochester N Y according to a member of the staff A wing of the clinic will be the James P Mitchell Foundation for Medical"
  ],
